<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="refresh" content="0;url=/">
  <title>BRUTALIMAGE Chrome Extension</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a0a0a, #1a1a1a);
      color: #fff;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .container {
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 500px;
    }
    .logo {
      width: 80px;
      height: 80px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00ffff, #ff0066);
      border-radius: 16px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      margin: 0 auto 24px;
      font-size: 40px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #000;
    }
    h1 { color: #00ffff; margin-bottom: 16px; }
    p { color: #888; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 16px 32px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #00ffff, #00cccc);
      color: #000;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin: 8px;
    }
    .info {
      margin-top: 32px;
      padding: 16px;
      background: rgba(0,255,255,0.1);
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(0,255,255,0.2);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="logo">B</div>
    <h1>BRUTALIMAGE Chrome Extension</h1>
    <p>Install BRUTALIMAGE as a Chrome extension or PWA for quick access.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn">Open Web App</a>
    <div class="info">
      <p><strong>How to install:</strong></p>
      <p>1. Open brutalimage.app in Chrome<br>
         2. Click the install icon in the address bar<br>
         3. Or use Menu → "Install BRUTALIMAGE"<br>
         4. The app will work offline!</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
